\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. deltoides} (L.) Glen,{\i  Bothalia}{\b  16:} 55 (1986) ({\i Mesembryanthemum deltoides} L., {\i Oscularia deltoides} (L.) Schwantes). Stems up to 50 cm, decumbent or trailing. Leaves 5-18 × 3-10 mm, triangular-obovoid, broadest above the middle, denticulate on the angles, pruinose. Flowers 1-3 together, 1-2 cm in diameter; petals purple. 2n = 18.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized on coastal rocks and walls in S.W. England} ({\i Isles of Scilly}). [Br.] ({\i South Africa}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. L. multiradiatus} (Jacq.) N.E. Br.,{\i  Gard. Chron}. ser. 3,{\b  87:} 71 (1930) ({\i L. roseus} (Willd.) Schwantes, {\i L. glaucus}  auct., non (L.) N.E. Br.). Stems up to 20 cm, decumbent, ascending or erect. Leaves 10-25 × 2-4 mm, linear-oblong, almost triangular in section, dark bluish-green. Flowers 1-3 together, 2-5 cm in diameter; petals pink to purplish-pink. 2n = 36.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, ana naturalized on coastal cliffs in the Channel Islands and S.W. Britain}. [Br Ga.] ({\i South Africa.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. L. falciformis} (Haw.) N.E. Br.,{\i  Gard. Chron.} ser. 3, {\b 87:} 212 (1930). Stems up to 80 cm, mostly procumbent but some erect. Leaves 6-8 × 1·5-4 mm, linear-oblong to falcate, generally more slender than those of{\b  2}, flattened above, obscurely keeled beneath pale bluish-green, pruinose. Flowers 1 or 2 together, 3·5-4·5 cm in diameter; petals pink or purple.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized on coastal cliffs and sands in W. Europe}. [Az Bl Br Ga Hb Lu.] ({\i South Africa}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b 2} and {\b 3} are very similar and are perhaps not distinct.
\par

